newsitem.title: USA: US WCoast prods ease on NYMEX, fundamentals strong.
newsitem.headline: US WCoast prods ease on NYMEX, fundamentals strong.

text.p: U.S. West Coast product prices eased under pressure from weak NYMEX gasoline and little buying interest as traders left the market early.
NYMEX October gasoline drifted 0.23 cent lower to 61.09 cents a gallon, weighed by high stocks and a seasonal decline in motorist demand.
The fall came on the heels of a 1.74-cent fall in gasoline futures on Thursday.
Fundamentally, traders saw low regional supplies reversing the downturn in prices, with 26.9 million barrels in stock last week, a fall of 709,000 barrels.
Conventional or "clear" grade gasoline in Los Angeles added another cent to yesterday's one-cent fall, hitting 64/65 cents a gallon. Discounts for San Francisco grade were two cents under.
And premium conventional in L.A. was 10 cents over regular on ongoing problems with key Mobil gasoline unit, and new rumors of a possible reformer problem at a Texaco plant.
CARB gasoline in L.A. fell two cents to 68.50/69 cents a gallon.
Bids for CARB diesel in L.A. decreased two cents 73.50/75 cents with low sulphur at off about two cents to 68.50/69.50 cents.
